    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 9, 1890</date>.
                            (Received September 25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 158.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your instructions by telegram of the 3d instant, which was received by me
                        per steamer from La Libertad on the 6th instant.</p>
                <pb facs="0201" n="97" xml:id="pg_97"/>
                <p>Anticipating these instructions, I had the honor to make a report to you as
                        full as possible in my dispatch No. 150 of August 29, 1890, concurrently
                        with that of Consul-General Hosmer’s No. 243 of the same date. If any
                        additional facts, however, come to my knowledge in relation to the same
                        matter, I shall promptly make you acquainted with them, and shall obtain an
                        affidavit of facts from Captain Pitts, commander of the Pacific Mail steamer
                            <hi rend="italic">Acapulco</hi>, when that vessel returns to the port of
                        San José.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing B. Mizner.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
